<H2>Components Window</H2>

<P>This Window shows all the components (movable files, directories or applications) that are installed as part of
a package (if there are any).</P>
<P>Select a package and press menu to see the following menu options.
<UL>
<LI>Create stub - create an application stub. This will forward the Help, Boot and Run
actions for an application to the real application and can be used as a short cut
to the application from another location on the disc. Available for applications only.</LI>
<LI>Create link - create a LinkFS symbolic link</LI>
<LI>Copy - make a copy the component</LI>
<LI>Move - move the component to another location. Checks are made that the component isn't moved into itself and then the <a href="movewnd.htm">Move window</a> is displayed to show the progress of the move.</LI>
<LI>Boot options - show the <A HREF="bootoptswnd.htm">Boot Options Window</A> that allows you to change the RISC OS startup options.</LI>
<LI>Boot - Run an applications !Boot file. Available for applications only.</LI>
<LI>Run - Run the component.</LI>
<LI>Help - Show an applications Help file. Available for applications only.</LI>
<LI>View - Open the directory that contains the component.</LI>
</UL>
</P>
<p>You can also run the component by double clicking on its icon. If you use the adjust
mouse button instead of the select mouse button the Applications Window will be
closed after the component is run.</p>
<p>Dragging an application icon to the filer will also create an application stub.</p>

</BODY>
